  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Write vertex form using the given vertex $(2, 5)$",
      "content": "$$f(x) = a(x-2)^2 + 5$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Solve for $a$ using point $(3, 24)$",
      "content": "$$24 = a(3-2)^2 + 5 \\implies 24 = a + 5 \\implies a = 19$$<br/>So $f(x) = 19(x-2)^2 + 5$."
    },
    {
      "title": "Compute $f(-1) - f(1)$",
      "content": "$$f(-1) = 19(-3)^2 + 5 = 171 + 5 = 176$$<br/>$$f(1) = 19(-1)^2 + 5 = 19 + 5 = 24$$<br/>$$f(-1) - f(1) = 176 - 24 = 152$$<br/><strong>C</strong> is correct."
    }
  ]
}